sp_scores.title: Defeat Borghen without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Borghen heals himself, which makes him one tough nut to crack, kupo! Use your party's muscle to hit him faster than he can keep up!
tip_battle.title: Borghen

dungeons.epilogue: Former count Borghen turned traitor prior to the Empire's invasion, going on to exploit his own people, forcing laborers to mine Mythril and construct the airship Dreadnought. Yet Firion and his comrades foiled Borghen at every turn, and he fell in an ambush set for the heroes at the Snow Cavern. His final act was to trigger a boulder trap, claiming the life of Josef.
dungeons.name: Snow Cavern (Return)
dungeons.prologue: Josef and Firion's team succeed in obtaining the Goddess's Bell within the Snow Cavern, but someone waits for them on their way out...

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Adamantoise's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Adamantoise is vulnerable to ice, kupo! Focused ice attacks will bring it down lickety-split!
tip_battle.title: Adamantoise

dungeons.epilogue: With the Dreadnought complete, the only course of action for the rebels was to cast Sunfire into its engine and cause a destructive chain reaction. Egil's Torch, used to carry the Sunfire, was held in Kashuan Keep, but only one of royal Kashuan blood or a bearer of the Goddess's Bell could access it. With the Kashuan prince Scott dead and his brother Gordon missing, the only option was to obtain the Goddess's Bell. Defeating the Adamantoise and claiming the bell, Firion, Josef, and the others prepared for the return journey.
dungeons.name: Snow Cavern
dungeons.prologue: Firion's next mission is to destroy the airship Dreadnought. To do that he will need the Goddess's Bell to enter Kashuan Keep. The team heads for the Snow Cavern where the bell is hidden.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Fire Gigas's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Fire Gigas has powerful single-target and area attacks, kupo! I highly recommend using Power Break and Magic Break to reduce that incoming damage! You also might want to exploit its weakness to ice attacks or just try to Paralyze the thing, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Fire Gigas

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's team had reached the third floor of the Mysidian Tower when their way was blocked by a mage who transformed into a massive Fire Gigas and attacked them. Though it was no easy battle, they defeated the gigas and continued up the tower.
dungeons.name: Mysidian Tower, Part 1
dungeons.prologue: Firion's team has escaped from Leviathan and reached the Mysidian Tower. Now they venture inside...

sp_scores.title: Defeat Gottos without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Gottos casts Haste on himself! Put the brakes on with Slow and Stop, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Gottos

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's team retook Castle Fynn by defeating the Palamecian commander Gottos. Even as the rebels celebrated their victory, Queen Hilda was concerned for Minwu, on a mission to Mysidia. With orders to find and aid Minwu, Firion's team obtained the White Mask beneath Castle Fynn and set off for Mysidia.
dungeons.name: Castle Fynn
dungeons.prologue: A rebellion coalesces around Queen Hilda and Prince Gordon, and while rebel forces are engaging the Empire elsewhere, Firion's team sneaks into Castle Fynn.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Captain without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Captain doesn't use any special attacks, kupo, but he doesn't have any particular weaknesses, either. Soften him up with Power Break and Armor Break, then lay on the debuffs and fight your way to victory!
tip_battle.title: Captain

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's party crossed a desert and infiltrated the Dreadnought, freeing Hilda and Cid from their cell to escape on Cid's airship. Continuing further into the Dreadnought, the party cast the Sunfire into the engine when the Dark Knight appeared. Though the knight's voice was oddly familiar to Maria, there was little time to dwell on this mystery as explosions enveloped the Dreadnought.
dungeons.name: Dreadnought
dungeons.prologue: Firion has returned to Altair together with Gordon, when he learns that Hilda has been captured by the Dreadnought. It falls to Firion to pursue the ship and rescue the princess!

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's team encountered a doppleganger in the Cave of Mysidia which they defeated by offering the White Mask to the goddess statue, then placing the Black Mask on the doppleganger. With the Crystal Rod in their possession, the party made for the Mysidian Tower.
dungeons.name: Cave of Mysidia
dungeons.prologue: With the Black Mask and White Mask in hand, Firion's team makes their way into the Cave of Mysidia in search of the Crystal Rod.

sp_scores.title: Defeath the Behemoth without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Behemoth packs some deadly physical attacks, kupo! Power Break and Protect will help take the edge off its attacks, and you may want to use debuffs, too!
tip_battle.title: Behemoth

dungeons.epilogue: Together with Prince Gordon, Firion's party came to the Coliseum where Queen Hilda was being held as a prize. Though they were victorious in the battle, their chances to rescue the queen and kill the Emperor were dashed when their true identities were revealed, and they were thrown into the dungeon. Rescue came in the guise of a thief, Paul, whom they'd previously saved when he was a prisoner at Semitt Falls. Returning Queen Hilda to Gordon, the party beat a quick retreat, fighting off their pursuers.
dungeons.name: Coliseum
dungeons.prologue: Firion returns to Altair to discover Queen Hilda acting strangely. She is revealed to be the Lamia Queen in disguise, whom the party defeats before heading to the Palamecian Coliseum where the real Hilda is being held captive.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Big Horn without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Big Horn boasts powerful physical attacks, kupo! Power Break and Protect will help take the edge off its attacks, and you may want to use debuffs, too!
tip_battle.title: Big Horn

dungeons.epilogue: On the Tropical Island Firion's team braved a vine-choked cavern. In the depths of the cavern they defeated the Big Horn, obtained the Black Mask, then set course for the Cave of Mysidia where the key to opening the tower could be found.
dungeons.name: Tropical Island
dungeons.prologue: Firion's team will need one more item in order to gain entry to the Mysidian Tower. They head for the Tropical Island in search of the Black Mask.

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's team defeated Thunder Gigas, the final guardian of the tower, and finally reached the top where Minwu awaited them. Minwu used all of his power to break the seal upon the Ultima tome, and was successful, though the exertion cost him his life.
dungeons.name: Mysidian Tower, Part 3
dungeons.prologue: Firion's team finally approaches the top of the Mysidian Tower and their prize: the Ultima Tome.

tip_battle.message: The Sergeant doesn't have any special attacks, but he doesn't have any particular vulnerabilities either. This battle will show what your party is really made of, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Sergeant

dungeons.epilogue: Princess Hilda welcomed Firion, Maria, and Guy into the ranks of the Wild Rose Rebellion following their successful infiltration of occupied Fynn. She then tasked them with finding Josef, an agent investigating the enchanted ore known as Mythril. In Semitt Falls, Firion's party succeeded in freeing Josef's daughter and the enslaved citizens of Salamand, securing enough Mythril ore to provide weapons for the rebellion.
dungeons.name: Semitt Falls Cavern
dungeons.prologue: Firion loses his parents in a Palamecian attack on Fynn. Now Firion, his friend Guy, and his sister Maria seek to join the rebellion against the Empire.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Roundworm without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Roundworm's Quake ability is a powerful attack that hits the entire party. It's a magic spell, so Silence will keep the ground from rocking, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Roundworm

dungeons.epilogue: When the storm subsided, the party found themselves inside the belly of the Leviathan. They proceeded through the beast, encountering the last surviving dragoon, Ricard. Though he mistrusted them at first, when he learned the party also sought the Ultima Tome, he joined them on their way to the Mysidian Tower.
dungeons.name: Leviathan
dungeons.prologue: The party approaches the Mysidian Tower, bearing the Crystal Rod that will grant them access, when they are caught in a storm and swallowed by the great Leviathan.

dungeons.epilogue: On the fifth floor the party once again encountered a mage. This time, the mage transformed himself into an Ice Gigas and attacked. Braving his icy assault, the party defeated the gigas and continued on to the next floor.
dungeons.name: Mysidian Tower, Part 2
dungeons.prologue: Having defeated the Fire Gigas, Firion's team continues up to the fourth floor of the Mysidian Tower.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Chimera without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Chimeras make for tough enemies, and they don't have any vulnerabilities, kupo! The worst part is, you have to fight four of them at once! Kupo-po! Use debuffs like Paralyze and Stop to keep their attacks to a minimum!
tip_battle.title: Chimera

dungeons.epilogue: Firion's party reached an old castle on Deist where a wyvern, poisoned by the Empire, begged them to sink its last egg in a life-giving pool deep within a cavern on the island. Firion helped the wyvern in hopes that the hatchling would, one day, help in the fight aginst the Empire.
dungeons.name: Deist Cavern
dungeons.prologue: The King of Fynn has ordered Firion to find the remnants of the Dragoons of Deist. Firion heads for Deist, fighting, then befriending, the pirate Leila along the way.
